{
  "doc_id": "36454",
  "text": "Anti-inflammatory treatments that affect macrophages may also be beneficial to AMD patients. In several studies of CNV patients, intravitreal injection of the antiinflammatory steroid triamcinolone has been shown to be beneficial, [CITATION_1] either alone or in conjunction with additional treatment modalities (eg, photodynamic therapy). [CITATION_2] Administration of triamcinolone by a synthetic implant was also found to be protective against experimental CNV in a rat model. [CITATION_3] It should be noted however that triamcinolone likely affects multiple intercellular pathways in addition to inflammation, and the modulation of these pathways (such as apoptosis) may be as important or more important than the impact of this steroid on inflammation.",
  "correct_citation": {
